1
00:00:10,377 --> 00:00:11,925
<i>(MAN CHATTERING)</i>

2
00:00:12,510 --> 00:00:15,439
<i>MAN.: See you Tuesday.
WOMAN.: How about right now?</i>

3
00:00:15,565 --> 00:00:17,741
<i>What? What?</i>

4
00:00:19,623 --> 00:00:20,586
<i>You wanna throw in the towel?</i>

5
00:00:20,628 --> 00:00:22,134
<i>No, I don't wanna
throw in the... towel!</i>

6
00:00:22,176 --> 00:00:23,975
<i>I thought
that's what you said!</i>

7
00:00:24,059 --> 00:00:25,816
<i>I'm not upset about anything!</i>

8
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,322
(DOOR OPENING)

9
00:00:28,201 --> 00:00:30,126
<i>Where the... are we going?</i>

10
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:31,464
What are you doing
down here?

11
00:00:31,506 --> 00:00:34,142
I thought you usually
had lunch with Coma Guy.

12
00:00:34,310 --> 00:00:36,904
This is Vegetative State Guy.
Better company.

13
00:00:37,490 --> 00:00:39,414
Hey, hey, tell him
about those Sherpas

14
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:41,590
you dropped acid with
in Saint Patrick's Cathedral.

15
00:00:41,674 --> 00:00:45,314
You stole my prescription pad
and you forged my name.

16
00:00:47,950 --> 00:00:49,707
What did you tell the cop?
I lied.

17
00:00:49,707 --> 00:00:51,172
They'd have put you away
for 10 years,

18
00:00:51,339 --> 00:00:53,431
after they took your license
to practice medicine.

19
00:00:53,515 --> 00:00:54,686
So, everything's good, then.

20
00:00:54,770 --> 00:00:56,778
I lied. To the cops.

21
00:00:56,820 --> 00:00:58,410
There is no case
unless they can prove

22
00:00:58,494 --> 00:01:01,213
that either
I got the drugs illegally
or I sold them illegally.

23
00:01:01,297 --> 00:01:03,305
I didn't do the second,
you lied about the first.
Game over.

24
00:01:03,431 --> 00:01:04,979
Yeah, Tritter's just playing.

25
00:01:05,021 --> 00:01:07,573
He's gonna see
how clever you are
and then just walk away.

26
00:01:07,657 --> 00:01:09,163
The important thing is
that you keep prescribing

27
00:01:09,205 --> 00:01:11,925
the same amount of drugs to me
or it'll look suspicious.

28
00:01:11,967 --> 00:01:13,222
Here's another way
to look at it,

29
00:01:13,264 --> 00:01:15,105
having forced me
to lie to the police,

30
00:01:15,146 --> 00:01:18,368
your first concern
is securing
your drug connection.

31
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:20,084
(DOOR OPENING)

32
00:01:23,724 --> 00:01:25,649
Joining my father for lunch?

33
00:01:26,151 --> 00:01:27,531
I should have called ahead
for a table.

34
00:01:27,657 --> 00:01:28,703
Dr. House was just...

35
00:01:28,745 --> 00:01:30,377
Enjoying a Reuben.

36
00:01:30,837 --> 00:01:31,841
It's okay.

37
00:01:32,385 --> 00:01:35,900
After 10 years,
anything that'll get doctors
in the same room as...

38
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,163
What are you doing?
Nothing.

39
00:01:39,247 --> 00:01:40,921
What are you doing?

40
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:44,351
Chips?

41
00:01:47,364 --> 00:01:49,916
Wanna see something
really cool?

42
00:01:56,402 --> 00:01:58,619
I saw you leaving
last Tuesday.

43
00:01:59,205 --> 00:02:01,339
You practically
tripped over two guys
on your way out,

44
00:02:01,381 --> 00:02:03,264
but you had no problem
opening doors.

45
00:02:03,264 --> 00:02:04,937
It's called akinetopsia.

46
00:02:05,439 --> 00:02:07,155
You can't see things
when they move.

47
00:02:07,238 --> 00:02:10,460
Now, since you haven't been
hit by a bus, I assume
that it's intermittent.

48
00:02:10,544 --> 00:02:11,925
It's probably
accompanied by seizures,

49
00:02:11,967 --> 00:02:15,230
which made me think that
I could set one off
by flashing the...

50
00:02:20,753 --> 00:02:23,096
God, I love this family.

51
00:03:00,879 --> 00:03:02,469
I can see fine now.

52
00:03:03,891 --> 00:03:07,071
I've had seizures before.
Most of the time
they're small.

53
00:03:07,155 --> 00:03:10,544
Doctors ran me through
all the tests.
Couldn't find anything.

54
00:03:10,628 --> 00:03:12,803
Any history of epilepsy
in your family?

55
00:03:12,845 --> 00:03:14,770
The only things I know
that run in my family are

56
00:03:14,812 --> 00:03:18,410
a lot of chutzpah
and the ability to sleep
for 10 years.

57
00:03:18,828 --> 00:03:20,293
Although
I'm not really an expert.

58
00:03:20,335 --> 00:03:22,301
Dad never really liked
my mother's side
of the family,

59
00:03:22,343 --> 00:03:26,276
and after she died
and he came here
I was raised by a guardian.

60
00:03:27,238 --> 00:03:29,372
I wouldn't even know
how to get in touch with them.

61
00:03:29,414 --> 00:03:30,962
How about your father's side
of the family?

62
00:03:30,962 --> 00:03:32,343
Any relatives
we could speak with?

63
00:03:32,343 --> 00:03:33,891
My father was an only child.

64
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:35,272
And my grandparents
are dead.

65
00:03:35,314 --> 00:03:36,444
Well, who did you put down

66
00:03:36,485 --> 00:03:39,247
as the person the hospital
should contact
in an emergency?

67
00:03:39,289 --> 00:03:40,293
I left it blank.

68
00:03:40,335 --> 00:03:41,967
There's gotta be someone,
a friend...

69
00:03:42,092 --> 00:03:43,180
I have plenty of friends.

70
00:03:43,264 --> 00:03:45,690
Just no one that would care
if I was here.

71
00:03:48,326 --> 00:03:50,753
Say, do you mind passing me
my backpack?

72
00:03:52,971 --> 00:03:54,310
(CLINKING)

73
00:04:05,021 --> 00:04:06,820
Hair of the dog.

74
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,883
CAMERON: Could be infection.
FOREMAN: Or a brain tumor.

75
00:04:12,050 --> 00:04:13,054
Says he had a CT.

76
00:04:13,138 --> 00:04:15,146
What's wrong
with the simplest explanation?
Trauma?

77
00:04:15,272 --> 00:04:16,402
He didn't report any injuries.

78
00:04:16,485 --> 00:04:18,410
He didn't report
being an alcoholic, either.

79
00:04:18,494 --> 00:04:21,046
Drinking equals falling down
equals trauma equals...

80
00:04:21,172 --> 00:04:22,176
Maybe it's inherited.

81
00:04:22,176 --> 00:04:25,607
How would you jump to genetics
from his EEG?

82
00:04:26,025 --> 00:04:28,326
All you've got
are some vaguely
epileptiform waves.

83
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:31,548
It's not his EEG.
It's his father's.

84
00:04:31,590 --> 00:04:34,477
When it comes
to cortical seizures,
like father, like son.

85
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:35,983
Small seizures
aren't unheard of

86
00:04:36,025 --> 00:04:37,448
in a patient
in a vegetative state.

87
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:38,996
Similarities
are interesting, though.

88
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,628
What caused
the vegetative state?

89
00:04:40,669 --> 00:04:42,301
His house burned down.

90
00:04:42,594 --> 00:04:43,933
Went back in to get his wife,

91
00:04:43,975 --> 00:04:45,523
firefighters
found him unconscious

92
00:04:45,607 --> 00:04:47,531
three feet from the bedroom,
asphyxiated.

93
00:04:47,615 --> 00:04:49,372
Not an inherited condition.

94
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:53,013
Test his DNA.
Start with
adrenomyeloneuropathy.

95
00:04:53,598 --> 00:04:55,272
Check out the home.

96
00:05:01,506 --> 00:05:02,929
He has a single bed.

97
00:05:03,013 --> 00:05:04,226
They still make single beds?

98
00:05:04,268 --> 00:05:06,109
It could mean
he just doesn't have sex,

99
00:05:06,192 --> 00:05:08,536
though there were condoms
in the apartment.

100
00:05:08,828 --> 00:05:11,506
House asked you
to check out
the home for toxins.

101
00:05:11,590 --> 00:05:13,808
No mold, no leaks, no pets.

102
00:05:13,891 --> 00:05:15,941
MRI and LP
are both inconclusive.

103
00:05:15,983 --> 00:05:17,824
Infection's still possible,
tumor's less likely, but...

104
00:05:17,908 --> 00:05:19,833
DNA?
The adrenomyeloneuropathy test

105
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:20,879
was negative.

106
00:05:20,962 --> 00:05:22,050
DNA test again.

107
00:05:22,176 --> 00:05:24,226
Try Unverricht-Lundborg
and late-onset Lafora's.

108
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:25,649
CHASE: Genetic tests
take forever.

109
00:05:25,732 --> 00:05:28,661
You can't just keep testing
for every inherited condition
you think it might be.

110
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:31,632
Well, not me.
I'll be leaving early.
But you guys can.

111
00:05:35,439 --> 00:05:38,912
You said no one's been sick
but what about
delivery people, repair guy?

112
00:05:38,996 --> 00:05:41,381
I wouldn't know.
I work from home.

113
00:05:41,925 --> 00:05:43,640
Haven't been to the office
in over a month.

114
00:05:43,724 --> 00:05:44,812
CAMERON: Visitors?

115
00:05:44,895 --> 00:05:46,067
Haven't had any.

116
00:05:46,109 --> 00:05:47,950
The only person
I've seen in the last week

117
00:05:47,992 --> 00:05:51,172
was the pizza delivery guy
and he looked pretty healthy.

118
00:05:51,632 --> 00:05:54,226
There's gotta be someone
you're close to.

119
00:05:54,728 --> 00:05:58,159
Actually, the person
I see most often
is my father.

120
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:02,092
He's asleep
so he can't stop me.

121
00:06:05,188 --> 00:06:06,318
(GROANS)

122
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,490
What is it?

123
00:06:07,531 --> 00:06:09,833
I'm just feeling
a little nauseous.

124
00:06:13,138 --> 00:06:14,561
I think his liver's failing.

125
00:06:14,644 --> 00:06:17,406
God. Does that mean
that I'm...

126
00:06:22,301 --> 00:06:23,347
We need a central line kit,

127
00:06:23,389 --> 00:06:26,444
two units of
packed red blood cells
type O Negative.

128
00:06:27,992 --> 00:06:29,874
He's unconscious
and heading for a coma.

129
00:06:29,916 --> 00:06:31,757
He's at a four
on the RLAS scale.

130
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:35,105
Stop all treatment.

131
00:06:35,397 --> 00:06:37,531
You think this is a reaction
to our meds?

132
00:06:37,573 --> 00:06:39,665
Well, they're obviously
not helping.

133
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,255
Given the fact
that he's an alcoholic,

134
00:06:41,297 --> 00:06:43,515
there's a good chance
his liver wasn't so hot
when he came in.

135
00:06:43,598 --> 00:06:45,774
Anti-seizure drugs
could have just pushed him
over the edge.

136
00:06:45,858 --> 00:06:48,368
We take him off those meds,
what do we put him on?

137
00:06:48,452 --> 00:06:49,456
I was hoping you'd know.

138
00:06:49,623 --> 00:06:52,720
It may be academic,
I just started him
on dialysis.

139
00:06:52,762 --> 00:06:56,402
Kidney and liver failure.
Not too many people
come back from that.

140
00:06:56,485 --> 00:06:58,619
Trauma's out of the picture.
Could still be infection.

141
00:06:58,703 --> 00:07:00,879
Or neurological...
Or genetic.

142
00:07:01,548 --> 00:07:04,059
We need a better history.

143
00:07:04,895 --> 00:07:07,992
Did you miss the part
where the patient
lost consciousness?

144
00:07:09,372 --> 00:07:11,255
L-dopa?

145
00:07:12,092 --> 00:07:14,644
You're not waking Kyle.
You're waking his father.

146
00:07:14,686 --> 00:07:16,653
I commend
your observational skills.

147
00:07:16,778 --> 00:07:17,782
You have no reason to think

148
00:07:17,866 --> 00:07:20,084
any amount of drugs
will wake a man from a coma.

149
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:21,883
Vegetative state.
Much easier.

150
00:07:21,967 --> 00:07:24,644
This guy's no Terry Schiavo,
his brain's all there,
he moves around,

151
00:07:24,770 --> 00:07:26,360
his muscles
have barely atrophied.

152
00:07:26,444 --> 00:07:28,661
He's just waiting
for a fairy-tale kiss.

153
00:07:28,703 --> 00:07:31,172
After I do that,
I'll stick a needle in him.

154
00:07:33,305 --> 00:07:36,025
The amount
of amphetamines alone
would be dangerous,

155
00:07:36,109 --> 00:07:38,201
besides
whatever the hell else
you've got in there.

156
00:07:38,201 --> 00:07:40,251
There are reports
out of South Africa

157
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:44,435
about a pill that would
temporarily revive someone
in a vegetative state.

158
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:47,029
<i>You've all seen Awakenings,
made me cry.</i>

159
00:07:47,657 --> 00:07:48,745
I wanna cry.

160
00:07:49,414 --> 00:07:50,921
CUDDY: Put the syringe down.

161
00:07:52,845 --> 00:07:55,105
I can outdraw you,
mysterious stranger.

162
00:07:55,188 --> 00:07:57,197
We don't experiment
on helpless patients.

163
00:07:57,239 --> 00:07:59,414
Be reasonable.
There's no way
this is gonna work.

164
00:07:59,498 --> 00:08:02,050
Even if you woke him,
it would only be
for a few hours.

165
00:08:02,092 --> 00:08:03,891
A day, two at the most.

166
00:08:03,975 --> 00:08:05,230
You're risking his life.

167
00:08:05,314 --> 00:08:08,075
I'm risking getting sued,
that's the only
objection here.

168
00:08:08,117 --> 00:08:10,502
You'll be torturing him
and his family.

169
00:08:11,046 --> 00:08:13,891
Well, good news for Legal,
the only family
he's got is upstairs dying.

170
00:08:13,933 --> 00:08:15,188
Hey!

171
00:08:22,845 --> 00:08:25,565
I want this patient monitored
for the next 24 hours.

172
00:08:25,649 --> 00:08:27,280
I want someone with him
at all times

173
00:08:27,322 --> 00:08:28,745
to make sure
you didn't kill him.

174
00:08:28,745 --> 00:08:31,004
I want your ass in my office.

175
00:08:31,046 --> 00:08:32,218
(MOANING)

176
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:35,272
God, I'm starving.

177
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:41,004
I could really go for a steak.

178
00:08:46,402 --> 00:08:49,247
Do you know your name?
Do you know where you are?

179
00:08:50,335 --> 00:08:53,180
Gabriel Wozniak.
I don't know the name
of this hospital.

180
00:08:53,305 --> 00:08:55,356
How much are three and five?

181
00:08:56,109 --> 00:08:57,239
Eight.

182
00:08:57,364 --> 00:09:01,255
Also known as half of 16,
a quarter of 32,
two to the third power.

183
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:04,059
Coolest thing ever.

184
00:09:04,059 --> 00:09:06,318
Any history of seizure
in your family?

185
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:08,117
No.
Liver disease?

186
00:09:08,117 --> 00:09:09,121
No.

187
00:09:09,205 --> 00:09:11,297
How long have I been here?
I...

188
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:14,100
I got the feeling
it's been a long time.

189
00:09:14,142 --> 00:09:15,188
Interesting.

190
00:09:15,230 --> 00:09:17,448
Your internal clock
kept ticking.

191
00:09:17,824 --> 00:09:19,958
How deep
does that awareness go?

192
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,339
Pick up scraps
of conversations?

193
00:09:21,423 --> 00:09:22,469
Do you have the vague sense

194
00:09:22,510 --> 00:09:24,435
that the
hospital administrator
dresses like a trollop?

195
00:09:24,519 --> 00:09:27,866
<i>Or that the new
Star Wars movies
were a disappointment?</i>

196
00:09:30,377 --> 00:09:32,762
I know my wife is dead.

197
00:09:36,987 --> 00:09:38,912
I don't know
how long it's been.

198
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,933
Ten years.

199
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:51,046
What's the last thing
you remember?

200
00:09:52,134 --> 00:09:53,515
The fire.

201
00:09:54,770 --> 00:09:57,155
My wife was in the bedroom,
she had taken a sleeping pill.

202
00:09:57,197 --> 00:10:01,004
I got Kyle out,
went back in for her.

203
00:10:02,845 --> 00:10:04,686
I knew I didn't make it.

204
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:06,109
I'm sorry.

205
00:10:06,653 --> 00:10:09,791
What about your wife's side
of the family?
Any history of seizures there?

206
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:12,469
Your son Kyle
is a patient here.

207
00:10:12,971 --> 00:10:16,444
I'm afraid
his condition is serious.
He may be dying.

208
00:10:19,958 --> 00:10:23,096
No seizure issues
on my wife's side, either.

209
00:10:23,891 --> 00:10:26,778
What about that steak?
Nobody ever answered me.

210
00:10:30,544 --> 00:10:31,506
(EXCLAIMS)

211
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:35,690
Rumor in the cafeteria
was Caustic Guy
was waking up Coma Guy.

212
00:10:35,774 --> 00:10:37,364
Technically,
Vegetative State Guy

213
00:10:37,448 --> 00:10:39,749
was woken by,
yeah, Caustic Guy.

214
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:40,795
So what happened?

215
00:10:40,879 --> 00:10:43,891
I gotta get him a steak
before I can ask him
any more questions.

216
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:45,272
He doesn't wanna talk
about his son?

217
00:10:45,314 --> 00:10:48,159
Didn't seem
to emotionally register
that his son is sick.

218
00:10:48,201 --> 00:10:49,247
Brain issue?

219
00:10:49,331 --> 00:10:51,883
He was asphyxiated,
spent 10 years as asparagus,

220
00:10:51,883 --> 00:10:54,059
who knows
what damage is in there.
It's possible.

221
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:56,234
Of course there's always
the simple explanation.

222
00:10:56,276 --> 00:10:58,368
Maybe he just
doesn't like his son.

223
00:10:58,661 --> 00:11:00,460
Only in your world
would that be simple.

224
00:11:00,544 --> 00:11:02,510
The delusion
that fathering a child

225
00:11:02,594 --> 00:11:04,854
installs a permanent geyser
of unconditional love...

226
00:11:04,937 --> 00:11:07,406
Maybe your father's feelings
were conditional,
not everyone's.

227
00:11:07,490 --> 00:11:08,494
Well, of course,
that would play into

228
00:11:08,619 --> 00:11:09,916
your romantic vision
of human...

229
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,297
In terms
you would understand,

230
00:11:11,339 --> 00:11:12,929
we have
an evolutionary incentive

231
00:11:12,971 --> 00:11:14,310
to sacrifice
for our offspring.

232
00:11:14,393 --> 00:11:17,364
Our tribe, our friends.
Keep them safe.

233
00:11:18,661 --> 00:11:20,795
Except for all the people
who don't.

234
00:11:21,172 --> 00:11:22,887
Everything is conditional.

235
00:11:23,724 --> 00:11:26,695
You just can't always
anticipate the conditions.

236
00:11:36,192 --> 00:11:38,243
Mind if we talk
for a few minutes?

237
00:11:39,623 --> 00:11:42,929
How many pills would you say
Dr. House takes a day?

238
00:11:44,142 --> 00:11:46,109
I'm uncomfortable
setting a number.

239
00:11:46,151 --> 00:11:47,573
Well, try.

240
00:11:48,745 --> 00:11:49,916
Six.

241
00:11:51,172 --> 00:11:52,343
A day?

242
00:11:54,184 --> 00:11:57,490
Has he ever had you
write prescriptions for him?

243
00:11:58,117 --> 00:12:00,167
No. What is it
you want me to say?

244
00:12:00,293 --> 00:12:02,510
That he takes too many pills
and is a danger
to the hospital,

245
00:12:02,594 --> 00:12:05,816
or he takes too few
because
he's selling them on the side?

246
00:12:05,858 --> 00:12:07,615
