251
00:12:17,113 --> 00:12:18,577
He's not even
much of a friend.

252
00:12:18,661 --> 00:12:21,590
Look how he left
Dr. Wilson holding the bag.

253
00:12:25,314 --> 00:12:28,494
It's odd.
You don't know about that?

254
00:12:28,996 --> 00:12:33,640
You defend him,
and he won't even tell you
what's happening in his life.

255
00:12:34,268 --> 00:12:35,774
(PAGER BEEPING)

256
00:12:45,021 --> 00:12:46,485
I was paged.

257
00:12:46,527 --> 00:12:47,615
We saw you with the cop.

258
00:12:47,615 --> 00:12:48,745
What'd he want?

259
00:12:48,828 --> 00:12:50,167
How many pills
does House take,

260
00:12:50,209 --> 00:12:51,381
did I ever write him
a prescription?

261
00:12:51,506 --> 00:12:52,971
That sort of stuff.

262
00:12:53,724 --> 00:12:55,941
I told him six.
A day or in a mouthful?

263
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:57,908
I was just hoping
you guys
would stay consistent with...

264
00:12:57,950 --> 00:12:59,498
He wants to talk to us, too?

265
00:12:59,582 --> 00:13:00,921
You're next.

266
00:13:02,636 --> 00:13:04,310
We've gotta tell House
what's going on.

267
00:13:04,351 --> 00:13:06,151
Tritter says no.
Then no it is.

268
00:13:06,234 --> 00:13:09,247
Cops have a thousand ways
to make life
difficult for you.

269
00:13:09,414 --> 00:13:11,464
Quick.
What's the kid's status?

270
00:13:11,506 --> 00:13:12,678
I gotta get back
to our sleeper

271
00:13:12,803 --> 00:13:15,439
before he goes looking
for the orgasmatron.

272
00:13:17,992 --> 00:13:19,874
See, if that were rhetorical,

273
00:13:19,916 --> 00:13:21,799
it would mean
that I can just turn around
and leave now,

274
00:13:21,883 --> 00:13:23,556
which I'm not doing,
from which
you should deduce...

275
00:13:23,598 --> 00:13:25,858
He's off all drugs
except the antibiotics.

276
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:27,741
His liver's just managing
to hang in there.

277
00:13:27,824 --> 00:13:29,916
He's still sliding into coma.

278
00:13:41,925 --> 00:13:43,556
Your barber sucks.

279
00:13:44,519 --> 00:13:47,699
Hey, Coma Diet,

280
00:13:47,741 --> 00:13:49,038
I could make a fortune.

281
00:13:49,163 --> 00:13:50,837
Vegetative State Diet.

282
00:13:50,879 --> 00:13:52,259
Who gave you your clothes?

283
00:13:52,301 --> 00:13:53,556
Dr. Cuddy.

284
00:13:53,766 --> 00:13:55,774
I guess I'll need
all new ones, anyway.

285
00:13:55,858 --> 00:13:57,322
Everything went in the fire.

286
00:13:57,406 --> 00:13:58,494
Don't worry about it.

287
00:13:58,577 --> 00:14:01,799
We use recyclable clothes now.
Wear them once, then eat them.

288
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,686
Your son's
measles vaccination,

289
00:14:04,728 --> 00:14:06,402
do you remember if he had it,
what type it was?

290
00:14:06,485 --> 00:14:08,870
Man, you're a piece of work,
you know that?

291
00:14:10,460 --> 00:14:12,385
You weren't gonna tell me,
were you?

292
00:14:12,510 --> 00:14:13,389
I don't need new clothes.

293
00:14:13,389 --> 00:14:16,151
Dr. Cuddy says
my body
will adjust to the drugs,

294
00:14:16,234 --> 00:14:18,159
that I'll be
a vegetable again
by tomorrow.

295
00:14:18,243 --> 00:14:20,711
If I'm really lucky,
the day after.

296
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:22,971
Yeah.

297
00:14:23,556 --> 00:14:24,477
If I've got a day to live,

298
00:14:24,561 --> 00:14:26,695
I'm not gonna spend it
