from the only family
he's got?

380
00:18:39,414 --> 00:18:42,218
No, this is no time
for you to do your thing.

381
00:18:42,343 --> 00:18:44,686
We don't care
about his state of mind,
we don't care if he's happy.

382
00:18:44,812 --> 00:18:47,239
This factory of yours,
what did you make?

383
00:18:51,004 --> 00:18:52,678
So ask me a question.

384
00:18:53,180 --> 00:18:54,226
I'm thinking.

385
00:18:54,268 --> 00:18:55,858
Only six left, by the way.

386
00:18:56,025 --> 00:18:58,536
So sign my name.
You don't need a doctor,
you need a pen.

387
00:18:58,619 --> 00:18:59,791
What is up with you two?

388
00:18:59,916 --> 00:19:03,096
Wilson lied to the bulls
to keep me
out of the big house.

389
00:19:03,138 --> 00:19:04,351
Are you out of your mind?

390
00:19:04,435 --> 00:19:05,941
Well, who's he gonna tell?

391
00:19:06,025 --> 00:19:09,121
By tomorrow night
he's gonna be
a mindless stalk of celery.

392
00:19:09,289 --> 00:19:12,050
Since I answered that one,
by the way, my turn.

393
00:19:12,134 --> 00:19:13,598
What did you make
in your factory?

394
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:14,937
Luxury boats.

395
00:19:16,067 --> 00:19:17,364
Have you ever been in love?

396
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:18,536
Wow!

397
00:19:18,619 --> 00:19:21,172
Going right for the closets
with the embarrassing stuff.
Good move.

398
00:19:21,255 --> 00:19:23,138
Yes. Describe the boats.

399
00:19:23,264 --> 00:19:26,946
Thirty-five to 65-foot hulls,
twin engines,
parquet floors in the galley,

400
00:19:26,987 --> 00:19:29,038
staterooms with queen beds.

401
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:31,925
How'd you meet?
She shot me.

402
00:19:32,427 --> 00:19:35,690
These boats, I assume you used
mildew-resistant paint
on the hulls?

403
00:19:35,732 --> 00:19:37,322
Naturally. Shot you?

404
00:19:37,866 --> 00:19:41,046
Paintball.
Doctors versus lawyers.

405
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:43,138
Did you ever take
your son to the factory?
Sure.

406
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:46,444
He used to run
all over the place,
but it was perfectly safe.

407
00:19:47,364 --> 00:19:48,996
Ever love anybody else?

408
00:19:49,749 --> 00:19:52,510
No more questions,
I got my answer.

409
00:19:52,552 --> 00:19:56,067
While Dad's in the office,
his son's
watching them spray-paint.

410
00:19:56,109 --> 00:19:57,866
And what kid wears a mask?

411
00:19:57,908 --> 00:20:00,628
Mercury specifically targets
the central nervous system.

412
00:20:00,669 --> 00:20:01,757
You're saying
this is my fault?

413
00:20:01,799 --> 00:20:04,059
Mercury poisoning
explains the seizures

414
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:05,983
and the liver's like
a big soup strainer.

415
00:20:06,025 --> 00:20:08,410
The soup runs through,
chicken dumplings stay.

416
00:20:08,452 --> 00:20:10,126
For soup, read blood,
for chicken...

417
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,632
I get it, I get it. Mercury.

418
00:20:11,632 --> 00:20:12,762
Sits more or less idle

419
00:20:12,803 --> 00:20:16,067
until your kid
pours tequila shooters
into his liver.

420
00:20:16,611 --> 00:20:19,665
When the liver goes,
takes out the kidneys,
explains everything.

421
00:20:19,707 --> 00:20:20,711
Yeah, it's me.

422
00:20:20,795 --> 00:20:23,598
<i>Foreman, draw blood.
Test for mercury poisoning.</i>

423
00:20:23,682 --> 00:20:25,565
Chase,
start heavy metal chelation

424
00:20:25,607 --> 00:20:27,364
while we're waiting
