431
00:20:47,657 --> 00:20:49,540
Ever write
any prescriptions for him?

432
00:20:49,623 --> 00:20:51,046
Yes.
Why?

433
00:20:51,172 --> 00:20:52,720
Did he tell you to?

434
00:20:53,264 --> 00:20:54,728
He asked me to.

435
00:21:01,548 --> 00:21:07,071
Medicine attracts people
who are attracted to power.

436
00:21:07,699 --> 00:21:11,632
I know how he hates
when he is defied
by a patient.

437
00:21:12,636 --> 00:21:16,109
I doubt he handles defiance
from his staff any better.

438
00:21:16,151 --> 00:21:18,033
Now you correct me
if I'm wrong,

439
00:21:18,117 --> 00:21:21,590
but I don't think
Dr. House asks for anything.

440
00:21:22,510 --> 00:21:24,435
I think he takes it.

441
00:21:24,519 --> 00:21:29,247
And I think that you are stuck
lying to the police

442
00:21:30,251 --> 00:21:33,766
to cover up something
you didn't wanna do.

443
00:21:41,757 --> 00:21:44,770
HOUSE: We have been
up and down St. James
like a Monopoly car.

444
00:21:44,812 --> 00:21:47,908
It's not here.
Giancarlo has
left the building.

445
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:53,808
We can still turn around
and go back to Princeton.

446
00:21:53,891 --> 00:21:56,485
No. We've come this far,
I'm getting the hoagie.

447
00:21:59,540 --> 00:22:01,548
If your son does
have mercury poisoning,

448
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:03,389
there's a good chance
he'll respond
to the chelation.

449
00:22:03,431 --> 00:22:05,649
You might be able to have
a few minutes with him
before you lapse.

450
00:22:05,732 --> 00:22:07,908
Why are you so concerned
about me?

451
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:11,799
Deep inside Wilson believes
that if he cares enough

452
00:22:11,883 --> 00:22:13,473
he'll never have to die.

453
00:22:14,059 --> 00:22:16,151
Your behavior isn't normal.

454
00:22:16,444 --> 00:22:17,908
And you would know normal?

455
00:22:17,992 --> 00:22:21,088
What could he have done
that you won't forgive
after 10 years?

456
00:22:21,172 --> 00:22:23,180
When this
is your last chance?

457
00:22:24,268 --> 00:22:26,360
My son is what he is.

458
00:22:26,444 --> 00:22:29,080
His mother's side,
all drunken losers.

459
00:22:30,418 --> 00:22:32,092
He's gone the same way.

460
00:22:33,013 --> 00:22:36,318
House told you drinking
had damaged your son's liver.

461
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:37,531
I just said that.

462
00:22:37,615 --> 00:22:38,870
But you didn't hear
him say that

463
00:22:38,954 --> 00:22:40,795
until after
we left the hospital.

464
00:22:40,837 --> 00:22:42,636
So why did you leave?

465
00:22:44,435 --> 00:22:46,778
Maybe your son
takes after your side.

466
00:22:47,615 --> 00:22:50,042
Seizures and an allergy
to emotional connections.

467
00:22:50,084 --> 00:22:51,841
Okay, okay, okay. Enough.

468
00:22:52,887 --> 00:22:55,732
We're in Atlantic City
and my time's not up yet.

469
00:22:55,774 --> 00:22:58,243
We find a hotel
