and cut out my heart."

682
00:33:49,372 --> 00:33:51,255
<i>Are you out of your mind?</i>

683
00:33:52,427 --> 00:33:54,770
Fine.
I'll think of something else.

684
00:33:56,402 --> 00:33:57,699
I'm sorry.

685
00:34:12,636 --> 00:34:15,565
Wilson, get out.

686
00:34:18,828 --> 00:34:19,791
No.

687
00:34:23,808 --> 00:34:25,858
You lied to the cops
enough for me.

688
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:32,469
Maybe I don't wanna
push this till it breaks.

689
00:34:54,728 --> 00:34:57,029
Pills are the simplest.

690
00:35:00,544 --> 00:35:03,054
Hanging has less chance
of damaging the heart.

691
00:35:06,527 --> 00:35:08,201
I'm okay with pain.

692
00:35:09,958 --> 00:35:12,510
Strangulation is better
than breaking your neck,

693
00:35:14,100 --> 00:35:15,900
which means this'll be slow.

694
00:35:19,247 --> 00:35:22,636
I wouldn't get to see him
even if we got in the car
right now

695
00:35:22,678 --> 00:35:25,649
and broke
the speed limit driving back,
would I?

696
00:35:26,485 --> 00:35:27,657
No.

697
00:35:30,795 --> 00:35:31,925
Tell him...

698
00:35:40,711 --> 00:35:42,762
I don't know
what to tell him.

699
00:35:46,653 --> 00:35:47,782
(SIGHS)

700
00:35:49,540 --> 00:35:51,632
I think it's my turn
to ask a question, isn't it?

701
00:35:51,716 --> 00:35:52,971
I don't think so.

702
00:35:53,264 --> 00:35:56,485
'Cause you just asked me
that thing
about the speed limit.

703
00:35:59,289 --> 00:36:00,921
What do you wanna know?

704
00:36:01,213 --> 00:36:04,770
If you could hear one thing
from your father,
what would it be?

705
00:36:06,904 --> 00:36:08,368
It wouldn't help you.

706
00:36:08,452 --> 00:36:09,582
Try me.

707
00:36:14,686 --> 00:36:16,360
I'd want him to say,

708
00:36:19,623 --> 00:36:21,172
"You were right.

709
00:36:22,510 --> 00:36:24,393
"You did the right thing."

710
00:36:26,611 --> 00:36:29,456
Yeah. It doesn't help.

711
00:36:44,937 --> 00:36:46,611
Hi.
Hi.

712
00:36:48,745 --> 00:36:50,167
I'm Dr. Wilson.

713
00:36:50,795 --> 00:36:52,385
I'm Mrs. Schaffer.

714
00:36:52,469 --> 00:36:54,100
I'm from Princeton.

715
00:36:55,272 --> 00:36:58,452
My husband and I
and our three children
live in Philadelphia.

716
00:37:02,259 --> 00:37:05,858
So, do you like to swing?

717
00:37:08,243 --> 00:37:09,582
No.

718
00:37:10,251 --> 00:37:12,971
Well, if you
change your mind, I'm in...

719
00:37:15,230 --> 00:37:17,197
House? House?

720
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:19,707
Is it room 622, 642?

721
00:37:20,042 --> 00:37:21,213
622.

722
00:37:21,925 --> 00:37:22,845
622.

723
00:37:23,515 --> 00:37:24,686
Yeah.

724
00:37:39,833 --> 00:37:40,962
Alibi.

725
00:37:43,431 --> 00:37:44,770
I figured.

726
00:37:53,013 --> 00:37:54,268
(THUMPING)

727
00:38:30,293 --> 00:38:33,096
They found
an open bottle of aspirin
by the body.

728
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:38,912
Lucky he had a headache,
reduced trauma
to the heart in transit.

729
00:38:40,460 --> 00:38:41,799
Lucky.

730
00:38:54,142 --> 00:38:55,690
That can't be all.

731
00:38:57,155 --> 00:38:59,038
Well, you got a heart
out of it.

732
00:38:59,163 --> 00:39:01,130
How many organs
do you want from the guy?

733
00:39:01,213 --> 00:39:03,598
I mean, my father
must have said something.

734
00:39:04,477 --> 00:39:05,900
He couldn't just...

735
00:39:05,983 --> 00:39:09,038
He must have given you
some kind of a message for me.

736
00:39:14,979 --> 00:39:16,820
He said you were right.

737
00:39:17,155 --> 00:39:18,870
You did the right thing.

738
00:39:23,933 --> 00:39:25,649
Right about what?

739
00:39:27,490 --> 00:39:29,121
What does that mean?

740
00:39:30,126 --> 00:39:32,887
How would I know?
He's your dad.

741
00:39:45,272 --> 00:39:47,992
You know
what I found interesting
about this case?

742
00:39:48,368 --> 00:39:50,753
That it proved
that people
can love unconditionally

743
00:39:50,837 --> 00:39:52,469
and you can tell yourself
it's not true,

744
00:39:52,552 --> 00:39:54,979
but you'll just end up
in a hotel room
in Atlantic City

745
00:39:55,063 --> 00:39:56,611
asking someone
to cut your heart out?

746
00:39:56,653 --> 00:39:58,703
(MACHINE BEEPING)
The hoagie.

747
00:39:58,703 --> 00:40:00,879
You thought this guy
was emotionally confused,

748
00:40:00,962 --> 00:40:02,678
and that the hoagie
was just a mask

749
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:05,272
to hide his real feelings
toward his son.

750
00:40:05,398 --> 00:40:06,527
It was.

751
00:40:06,904 --> 00:40:09,540
Did you know Tritter
was talking to your team
while we were away?

752
00:40:09,540 --> 00:40:10,544
Yeah.

753
00:40:11,088 --> 00:40:12,427
And yet you moved
Heaven and Earth

754
00:40:12,469 --> 00:40:15,356
to get him that mask
with mustard and prosciutto.

755
00:40:15,398 --> 00:40:16,862
Which one of them told you?

756
00:40:16,946 --> 00:40:17,908
All of them.

757
00:40:17,992 --> 00:40:20,586
Which means that none of them
said anything
I have to worry about.

758
00:40:20,628 --> 00:40:21,841
(MACHINE BEEPING)
Back to the hoagie.

759
00:40:21,925 --> 00:40:23,891
You think that
my addiction's out of hand.

760
00:40:23,975 --> 00:40:27,741
Your need to be needed
is so strong that you'll
give people what they want,

761
00:40:27,782 --> 00:40:29,456
what they need,
what they think they need.

762
00:40:29,540 --> 00:40:33,180
I don't think my enabling
is anything you should be
complaining about.

763
00:40:33,557 --> 00:40:35,649
Yes, my name
is Dr. James Wilson,

764
00:40:36,151 --> 00:40:38,828
account number 835687.

765
00:40:39,665 --> 00:40:41,799
The ATM says
I've got zero...

766
00:40:43,473 --> 00:40:45,230
What does that mean, a hold?

767
00:40:48,285 --> 00:40:50,209
Yeah, okay, thanks.

768
00:40:54,226 --> 00:40:55,398
(SIGHS)

769
00:40:55,439 --> 00:40:59,289
My accounts have been frozen
as part of
a police investigation.

770
00:41:02,510 --> 00:41:04,561
They can't keep
your money forever.

771
00:41:06,025 --> 00:41:10,000
No, they can keep it
till I agree to help send
you to prison for 10 years.

772
00:41:15,021 --> 00:41:16,862
You're getting dinner.



